    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6276" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μίτρη</span></b> : a <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">band</span>
          or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">girdle</span> round the waist and abdomen, below the
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">στατὸς θώρηξ</span>, the exterior of metal
          plates, the interior lined with wool (see cut No. 33), shorter than
          the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ζῶμα</span>, which covered it, while over
          both and the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θώρηξ</span> passed the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ζωστήρ</span>. (See cut No. 3.)</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
